incident_updates.body:
The cooling system is back in place.
Our teams are currently putting back progressively the servers into service.

Due to a malfunction on the cooling system, the racks R715A16 and R715A17 are currently unavailable.
The technical teams estimate that the cooling system will be back in service within 1H30.
From there, the servers will be progressively brought back into service.
We apologize for the inconvenience caused

All the servers of rack R715A14  and R715A13 are up and running.
Our teams are currently working on the other racks which are as follow: R715A16 and R715A17.
Servers of rack R715A17 are verified by our teams and seems to have a limited impact.
We apologize for the inconvenience and thank you for your understanding

R715A15 rack is functional
Rack R715A14 and R715A13 are being restored (75% of the servers are working again)
Rack R715A16 and R715A17 must be fully checked by our technical teams. If the servers are intact, they will be put back into service.
In case of hardware failure, the hardware will be replaced. Due to the integral check, the return to service of the servers can take some time. We will inform you as soon as we have more visibility on the status of these two racks.
Update :Private and public network are also unreachable for R715A14 and R715A13. We apologize for the inconvenience caused.
Start time : 20/04/2022 12:12 UTC Service impact : Both public and private network are unreachable for R715A16 and R715A17. Ongoing actions : Our teams are currently working to solve the problem.

Service improvement: The indexation backend of Logs Data Platform will be replaced from Elasticsearch to OpenSearch. Kibana instances will be replaced by OpenSearch Dashboards ones. APIv6 calls related to ElasticSearch backend will be automatically redirected to new OpenSearch backend and will remain available until September 2022. The following documentation : https://docs.ovh.com/fr/logs-data-platform/ will be updated few days before the migration.

scheduled_maintenances.name: [GRA, RBX, SBG, BHS / France, Canada][ Cisco ASA firewall]  Baremetal  Cisco ASA firewall  Planned Service End of Life

incident_updates.body: Start time : 28/02/2022 10:00 UTC Service impact : As part of the product lifecycle management we plan to end the baremetal service of Cisco ASA firewall by August 31, 2022. This service interruption will concern only the customers who have previously subscribed to this service. OVHcloud will decommission the service so that you wont be able to connect to your Cisco ASA firewall from that date. Please make the appropriate backup of your data prior that date. --------------------------------------------------- Heure de dbut : 28/02/2022 10:00 UTC Impact du service : Dans le cadre de la gestion du cycle de vie des produits, nous prvoyons de mettre fin au service baremetal du pare-feu Cisco ASA au 31 aout 2022. Cette interruption de service ne concernera que les clients qui ont prcdemment souscrit ce service. OVHcloud mettra le service hors service de sorte que vous ne pourrez plus vous connecter votre pare-feu Cisco ASA partir de cette date. Veuillez effectuer les sauvegardes appropries de vos donnes avant cette date.
Scheduled maintenance is currently in progress. We will provide updates as necessary.
Maintenance will begin as scheduled in 60 minutes.
